01:51.217 --> 01:57.656
♪ No, I can't take
one more step towards you ♪

01:57.745 --> 02:02.849
♪ 'cause all that's waiting
is regret ♪

02:04.852 --> 02:10.257
♪ don't you know
I'm not your ghost anymore ♪

02:10.358 --> 02:15.195
♪ you've lost the love
I love the most ♪

02:17.331 --> 02:23.303
♪ I've learned to live
half alive ♪

02:23.404 --> 02:30.777
♪ and now you want me
one more time ♪

02:30.878 --> 02:33.280
♪ and who do you
think you are? ♪

02:33.381 --> 02:37.050
♪ running around,
leaving scars ♪

02:37.151 --> 02:40.554
♪ collecting
your jar of hearts ♪

02:40.655 --> 02:43.690
♪ and tearing love apart

02:43.791 --> 02:49.930
♪ you're gonna catch a cold
from the ice inside your soul ♪

02:50.031 --> 02:53.099
♪ so don't come back for me

02:53.201 --> 02:57.804
♪ who do you think you are?

02:57.905 --> 03:04.244
♪ Who do you think you are?

03:04.345 --> 03:10.684
♪ Who do you think you are?

03:10.785 --> 03:16.790
♪ Who do you think you are?

03:16.891 --> 03:21.928
♪ Who do you think you are?

03:22.029 --> 03:23.263
Lacey: You okay?!

03:23.364 --> 03:24.598
Evan: He's still here?!

03:24.699 --> 03:26.566
He better not be!
My poor baby!

03:26.667 --> 03:28.134
How are the kids?
How are they taking it?

03:28.236 --> 03:29.469
Are they all right?
They're okay.

03:29.570 --> 03:30.604
They were pretty upset
when I told them.

03:30.705 --> 03:33.006
Well, join the club.
And he just showed up?!

03:33.107 --> 03:35.175
The nerve to show his face in this house!
No word, no warning, no nothing?!

03:35.276 --> 03:37.393
If it was me, I would've
kicked his ass so hard,

03:37.394 --> 03:38.468
Oh, kicking would have been
too good for him.

03:38.469 --> 03:39.569
he's gonna have to strap
a pillow onto it to sit down.

03:40.914 --> 03:43.782
I swear, if he wasn't my brother...
Hey, where'd she go?

03:43.883 --> 03:46.852
[ Knock on door ]

03:48.455 --> 03:49.755
Morning.

03:57.030 --> 04:00.432
I got to get to work.

04:07.653 --> 04:11.163
Yeah, maybe I'll just, uh...
come back later.

04:11.263 --> 04:13.097
You've got some explaining to do.
I'll say.

04:13.114 --> 04:14.715
Y'all both deserve
an explanation.

04:14.816 --> 04:16.817
All right, I just feel like
I owe it to Riley

04:16.918 --> 04:18.552
to talk to her first.

04:18.653 --> 04:20.921
Hey.
I got to get to work.

04:21.856 --> 04:23.624
Thank you for
looking after the kids.

04:23.725 --> 04:25.859
Don't worry. I won't leave him
alone with the kids for a second.

04:38.373 --> 04:40.374
[ Birds chirping ]

04:48.016 --> 04:50.283
[ Sighs ]

05:08.503 --> 05:11.171
[ Birds chirping ]

05:11.272 --> 05:13.306
Georgia,
Kyle came home last night.

05:13.408 --> 05:16.176
What?!
Oh, I can't believe him!

05:16.277 --> 05:18.679
Crazy, right?
Well, why didn't you call me?

05:18.780 --> 05:20.280
I don't know.
I guess I was just...

05:20.381 --> 05:23.271
in shock, and I needed
to let it sink in.

05:23.296 --> 05:23.984
And?

05:23.985 --> 05:25.919
Well, I'm confused
and frustrated

05:26.020 --> 05:28.221
and so furious
that I could just spit.

05:28.322 --> 05:31.324
Come on.
I got just the thing for you.

05:31.426 --> 05:32.959
Come on.

05:33.061 --> 05:34.194
Okay.

05:34.295 --> 05:35.796
[ Birds chirping ]

05:35.897 --> 05:38.231
So, what are we doing
out here?

05:38.332 --> 05:39.366
Hit it.

05:39.467 --> 05:40.467
Excuse me?

05:40.568 --> 05:42.703
We're at the back
of Buckey's Appliances.

05:42.804 --> 05:44.538
Buckey and I,
we got a little deal.

05:44.639 --> 05:46.306
It's called
release quid pro quo.

05:46.407 --> 05:48.442
So, hit it!

05:48.543 --> 05:50.944
Okay.

05:51.045 --> 05:52.279
Do it like you mean it!

05:52.380 --> 05:54.481
Okay.

05:54.582 --> 05:56.316
Good girl!
Hit it!

05:56.417 --> 05:57.918
Come on, now,
knock it out!

05:58.019 --> 05:59.419
There you go!

05:59.520 --> 06:01.988
Whoo! Whoo!

06:02.090 --> 06:03.590
It feels good!

06:03.691 --> 06:04.591
[ Laughs ]

06:04.692 --> 06:05.659
Okay, you go.

06:05.760 --> 06:07.094
Wait a minute.

06:07.195 --> 06:09.496
[ Both laugh ]
Oh, hell no!

06:09.597 --> 06:10.731
[ Laughs ]
Whoo!

06:10.832 --> 06:12.966
This is for
Kyle Parks leaving!

06:13.067 --> 06:14.968
And that's
for coming home!

06:15.069 --> 06:16.436
[ Shouts ]

06:16.537 --> 06:18.071
Whoo!

06:18.172 --> 06:19.139
There you go!

06:19.240 --> 06:20.507
[ Exhales sharply ]

06:20.608 --> 06:22.008
That was good, girl.

06:22.110 --> 06:23.510
We'd better
get back inside.

06:23.611 --> 06:25.212
Just one more.
One more.

06:25.313 --> 06:27.814
And...

06:27.915 --> 06:30.951
He shouldn't even be in
this house for one more second.

06:31.052 --> 06:32.385
I think you should
kick him out.

06:32.487 --> 06:33.520
Why don't you
kick him out?

06:33.621 --> 06:35.956
Because he's not
my son-in-law. That's why.

06:36.057 --> 06:37.691
Well, he's your best friend's
deadbeat husband.

06:37.792 --> 06:39.226
I can't think
of a better reason.

06:39.327 --> 06:40.994
Deadbeat.

06:41.095 --> 06:43.497
Yeah,
I guess I deserve that.

06:43.598 --> 06:44.998
Well, it's true,
isn't it?

06:45.099 --> 06:47.100
No, it's not.

06:47.201 --> 06:48.401
You left.

06:48.503 --> 06:50.337
And you have the gall
to show your face in here again.

06:50.438 --> 06:52.038
I mean,
what were you thinking?

06:52.140 --> 06:54.207
When you and Riley
were 16 years old,

06:54.308 --> 06:57.444
I supported you.

06:57.545 --> 06:59.112
I protected you.

06:59.213 --> 07:00.347
I defended you.

07:00.448 --> 07:02.215
And when you had a fight,

07:02.316 --> 07:04.151
I told Riley
she had to stick it out

07:04.252 --> 07:06.653
because that's the way marriage
is supposed to be.

07:06.754 --> 07:09.389
I know, Linette.

07:09.490 --> 07:11.758
I can't tell you
how much I appreciated that.

07:11.859 --> 07:14.294
I treated you
like you were my own son.

07:14.395 --> 07:16.763
My family welcomed you
with open arms,

07:16.864 --> 07:18.064
and what do you do?

07:18.166 --> 07:20.901
You turn around and walk out.
I got this.

07:21.002 --> 07:23.370
It's my turn now.

07:23.471 --> 07:26.840
Do you have any idea
what you've done here,

07:26.941 --> 07:30.243
how much you've hurt Riley,
the kids, Evan?

07:30.344 --> 07:33.046
You think it's easy
to keep a family going?

07:33.147 --> 07:36.216
It has taken a village,
and Riley has led the way,

07:36.317 --> 07:38.919
doing more
than any one person should.

07:39.020 --> 07:42.656
My God, Dale was out looking
for you every mile he drove.

07:42.757 --> 07:44.991
We were all
out of our minds with worry,

07:45.092 --> 07:47.093
and you don't even
have the decency

07:47.195 --> 07:48.962
to send word
that you're okay?

07:49.063 --> 07:52.199
I just -- I don't even know
what to say to you.

07:52.300 --> 07:54.734
Except, shame on you.

07:57.138 --> 07:58.371
I'm sorry.

08:00.141 --> 08:02.075
Look, I know that doesn't mean
anything to y'all right now.

08:02.176 --> 08:04.945
But I am.

08:06.948 --> 08:10.050
Now, can I at least
take the kids to school?

08:10.151 --> 08:12.052
It's summer break.

08:16.190 --> 08:18.191
[ Birds chirping ]

08:23.064 --> 08:24.164
Riley:
Is everything okay?

08:24.265 --> 08:25.532
I sure hope so, sugar,

08:25.633 --> 08:28.668
'cause my spidey sense
is a-tingling something awful.

08:28.769 --> 08:30.170
Uh-oh,
that can't be good.

08:30.271 --> 08:31.238
Well, it's not.

08:31.339 --> 08:32.905
It has to do with
my friend Clifton

08:33.006 --> 08:34.241
and the Sugar Land police.

08:34.342 --> 08:35.542
I think
they might be after me.

08:35.643 --> 08:36.676
Georgia, are you sure?

08:36.777 --> 08:38.144
'Cause I know sometimes
I get that feeling.

08:38.246 --> 08:39.980
Turns out just to be
my overactive imagination.

08:40.081 --> 08:42.982
Well, I'm inclined
to agree with you,

08:43.083 --> 08:45.118
except it was confirmed
by another friend.

08:45.219 --> 08:46.386
What'd they say?

08:46.487 --> 08:49.322
Well, somebody's got a burr
under their saddle about me.

08:49.423 --> 08:51.091
Well,
what are you gonna do?

08:51.192 --> 08:53.660
Well, I'm gonna
have to step back, you know,

08:53.761 --> 08:54.928
leave town for awhile.

08:55.029 --> 08:57.097
I don't know when was
the last time I took a vacation.

08:57.198 --> 08:59.065
Oh, that sounds great.

08:59.166 --> 09:00.667
How long
are you gonna be gone?

09:00.768 --> 09:03.169
Until it all blows over --
a couple of weeks at least.

09:03.271 --> 09:04.304
I am so envious.

09:04.405 --> 09:06.239
Hey, who are you gonna get
to run this place?

09:06.340 --> 09:08.508
Well, that's what I wanted
to talk to you about.

09:08.609 --> 09:11.544
I want you
to run the spa.

09:14.982 --> 09:16.549
I don't know what to say.

09:16.651 --> 09:18.151
Well, how about a "yes"?

09:18.252 --> 09:20.654
Remember,
I am not giving it to you.

09:20.755 --> 09:23.484
This is temporary,
and I am coming back.

09:23.509 --> 09:24.324
Well, you'd better.

09:24.325 --> 09:28.061
In that file cabinet
filed under "Christmas gifts,"

09:28.162 --> 09:32.399
there's a little book
with some very big names in it.

09:32.500 --> 09:34.434
The client list?

09:34.535 --> 09:37.003
I want you to take it
when you leave tonight

09:37.104 --> 09:39.706
and put it someplace else
only you know about,

09:39.807 --> 09:40.740
someplace safe.

09:40.841 --> 09:42.309
Okay, why would I want
to do that?

09:42.410 --> 09:44.778
Well, think of it as the secret
codes in all those movies,

09:44.879 --> 09:46.513
you know,
the ones with the big bombs.

09:46.614 --> 09:49.349
Only the person in charge
know the codes

09:49.450 --> 09:50.483
and where they are.

09:50.584 --> 09:51.518
Georgia,
that sounds scary.

09:51.619 --> 09:52.786
I'm not gonna have to use it,
am I?

09:52.887 --> 09:55.221
Lord, no.
This is just a precaution.

09:55.323 --> 09:58.391
God forbid something happens
to me while I'm away.

09:58.492 --> 10:00.727
Georgia, don't even joke
about things like that.

10:00.828 --> 10:02.963
Well, I am just saying,
it is best to be prepared.

10:03.064 --> 10:06.266
It wasn't raining
when Noah built the Ark.

10:06.367 --> 10:07.567
You know that.

10:12.344 --> 10:13.845
Kyle: I really appreciate
you meeting me.

10:13.946 --> 10:15.346
I think
you're the only one in town

10:15.447 --> 10:16.681
that's talking to me
right now.

10:16.782 --> 10:18.883
I'm surprised Lacey's
even letting you see me.

10:18.984 --> 10:21.419
Yeah, she's not
your biggest fan.

10:21.520 --> 10:22.787
So, what's the deal, man?

10:22.888 --> 10:25.623
Are you...back?

10:25.724 --> 10:29.060
Hon-honestly,
I have no idea.

10:29.161 --> 10:31.029
I mean,
I-I didn't think about

10:31.130 --> 10:32.630
how hard
this was all gonna be.

10:32.731 --> 10:36.067
You walked out on your wife
and kids for a year.

10:36.168 --> 10:38.202
What did you think?

10:38.304 --> 10:41.039
I thought she would
at least talk to me,

10:41.140 --> 10:42.440
listen
to what I had to say.

10:42.541 --> 10:43.942
Yeah.

10:44.043 --> 10:45.743
I mean,
I-I don't know what to do.

10:45.844 --> 10:47.812
What do I do?
How do I make her hear me?

10:47.913 --> 10:49.213
I'm sorry.

10:49.315 --> 10:51.549
How do you make her
hear you?

10:51.650 --> 10:53.184
Are we still talking about
the same woman?

10:53.285 --> 10:55.386
You don't make Riley
do anything.

10:55.487 --> 10:58.690
I think what you need to do
is just...I don't know.

10:58.791 --> 11:01.526
Just do whatever it takes
to win her back.

11:01.627 --> 11:03.161
Yeah.

11:03.262 --> 11:04.562
And don't ask me
what kind of flowers are good

11:04.663 --> 11:05.897
in this kind of situation.

11:05.998 --> 11:08.299
You are right.

11:09.868 --> 11:12.103
Yeah.

11:12.204 --> 11:15.239
Hindsight is a bitch,
isn't it?

11:15.341 --> 11:17.709
Yeah.

11:21.046 --> 11:23.548
I have family
down on St. Simons Island.

11:23.649 --> 11:26.317
I'll be there on the beach,
watching the waves.

11:26.418 --> 11:28.019
For how long?
A few weeks at least.

11:28.120 --> 11:31.022
Also, I'm putting Riley
in charge while I'm gone.

11:31.023 --> 11:31.708
When are you leaving?

11:31.733 --> 11:34.092
I have a few loose ends
to tie up -- probably tomorrow.

11:34.093 --> 11:35.159
What if I --
what if we need

11:35.260 --> 11:36.661
to get ahold of you
while you're gone?

11:36.762 --> 11:38.296
There is no need for that.

11:38.397 --> 11:40.865
Just talk to Riley.
She'll be handling everything.

11:40.966 --> 11:42.500
So, as of right now,

11:42.601 --> 11:47.138
all of you should think
and treat her as if she is me.

11:49.141 --> 11:50.341
Look out for sharks.

11:50.442 --> 11:52.944
Riley,
your 2:00 is waiting.

11:53.045 --> 11:54.445
It's Earl.
It's a straight massage.

11:54.546 --> 11:56.681
I can take him if you need
to go over stuff with Georgia.

11:56.782 --> 11:58.549
Oh, no. He's one
of my favorite clients,

11:58.651 --> 12:00.752
but thank you.

12:02.421 --> 12:03.955
You go get him, girl.

12:04.056 --> 12:05.256
[ Door opens ]

12:07.660 --> 12:10.028
You know, Earl, I keep telling
you I'm a professional.

12:10.129 --> 12:11.562
You don't have to keep
your shirt on.

12:11.664 --> 12:13.865
Only person sees me naked
is my wife.

12:13.966 --> 12:15.166
[ Laughs ]

12:15.267 --> 12:17.969
And the last time that happened,
Johnson was President.

12:18.070 --> 12:19.971
Oh, come on. A good-looking guy
like yourself?

12:20.072 --> 12:21.039
I am shocked.

12:21.140 --> 12:22.507
Well, her loss, I say.

12:22.608 --> 12:24.509
You play your cards right,

12:24.610 --> 12:26.544
and you could be
the second Mrs. Hudson.

12:26.645 --> 12:27.979
Oh, well,
be still, my heart.

12:28.080 --> 12:29.013
[ Chuckles ]

12:29.114 --> 12:30.415
Okay, what are we gonna
work on today?

12:30.516 --> 12:32.750
Uh,
my hip's acting up again.

12:32.851 --> 12:35.520
I think I got a hitch
in my giddyap.

12:35.621 --> 12:38.289
Okay, well, let's see
if we can't unhitch it.

12:40.492 --> 12:41.993
Okay.

12:42.094 --> 12:44.829
You ready, Earl?

12:44.930 --> 12:46.564
Earl?

12:49.435 --> 12:51.536
Earl?

12:54.540 --> 12:57.275
Earl?!

13:22.301 --> 13:23.601
Sarah said
you wanted to see me.

13:23.702 --> 13:25.436
Yes.
What's wrong?

13:25.537 --> 13:26.637
You look like
you've seen a ghost.

13:26.739 --> 13:28.806
Interesting choice
of words.

13:28.907 --> 13:32.043
Um, I have a problem,
and I need to talk to you.

13:32.144 --> 13:33.144
Well,
just spit it out, hon.

13:33.245 --> 13:34.245
We can deal with anything.

13:34.346 --> 13:35.413
I just need to know
what it is first.

13:35.514 --> 13:37.148
You know my client,
Earl?

13:37.249 --> 13:38.916
Yeah.

13:39.017 --> 13:40.918
Uh, he's on my table...

13:41.019 --> 13:42.053
dead.

13:42.154 --> 13:44.088
What do you mean "dead"?

13:45.457 --> 13:47.992
As in not living.

13:48.093 --> 13:51.262
Are you kidding me?

13:51.363 --> 13:54.031
In all my years,
this is definitely a first.

13:54.133 --> 13:55.500
Okay,
what are we gonna do?

13:55.601 --> 13:56.667
Oh, hell, I don't know.

13:56.769 --> 13:58.503
Uh, call 911?

13:58.604 --> 14:01.739
Well, it's not really
an emergency anymore, is it?

14:01.840 --> 14:05.576
Uh, what about, uh, Fred
down at Bouchard's Mortuary?

14:05.677 --> 14:08.679
I don't know if his family
would want to do that.

14:08.781 --> 14:10.448
Oh!
His emergency contact number.

14:10.549 --> 14:11.549
Perfect.

14:13.719 --> 14:16.053
This is a lovely place.

14:16.155 --> 14:20.158
Earl's always talking about
how nice everyone is.

14:20.259 --> 14:22.693
T-that's great,
Mrs. Hudson.

14:22.795 --> 14:24.362
Oh, please, call me Ruth.

14:24.463 --> 14:27.431
Well, it's been lovely
talking to you ladies,

14:27.533 --> 14:30.902
but I really do need to get
to Olsen's before it closes.

14:31.003 --> 14:33.704
Uh, when do you think
Earl will be finished?

14:33.806 --> 14:36.607
Well...

14:36.708 --> 14:40.311
Ruth, Earl is, uh...

14:40.412 --> 14:42.814
...Earl is done...

14:43.949 --> 14:45.416
...for good.

14:46.385 --> 14:47.552
What do you mean, dear?

14:49.221 --> 14:51.622
Go on, girl.
Just rip the band-aid off fast.

14:51.723 --> 14:52.957
Okay.

14:53.058 --> 14:54.392
Earl is dead.

14:56.228 --> 14:57.895
Ruth, honey, you okay?

14:59.364 --> 15:02.366
Oh, my God, she's in shock.

15:02.467 --> 15:05.303
I know. This must be
so difficult for you.

15:07.272 --> 15:09.507
[ Laughing ]
Are you kidding?!

15:09.608 --> 15:12.510
It's the best news
I've had in 50 years!

15:17.349 --> 15:19.517
[ Chuckles ]

15:24.389 --> 15:26.157
Do you want to be alone?

15:26.258 --> 15:27.425
Not particularly.

15:27.526 --> 15:28.793
Oh.

15:28.894 --> 15:30.628
Okay, well, I just thought maybe
you'd want to say goodbye.

15:30.729 --> 15:33.464
I said sayonara to Earl
50 years ago.

15:33.565 --> 15:37.068
I married Earl
when I was 19.

15:37.169 --> 15:39.203
Oh, the first couple of years
were good enough.

15:39.304 --> 15:41.505
Then,
like a quality bathtub,

15:41.607 --> 15:44.675
the love went
straight down the drain.

15:44.776 --> 15:45.843
Yet you stayed.

15:45.944 --> 15:48.613
Why didn't you leave
or get a divorce?

15:48.714 --> 15:50.915
In my day, dear,
you didn't do those things.

15:51.016 --> 15:53.718
Instead, I got Bud.

15:53.819 --> 15:57.121
Aww. A dog?
They do make great companions.

15:57.222 --> 15:59.624
Oh, no.
Bud is my lover.

15:59.725 --> 16:03.361
[ Chuckles ]
And he treats me real nice.

16:03.462 --> 16:06.130
He takes me to Cracker Barrel
every Sunday morning.

16:06.231 --> 16:09.634
[ Sighs ] The things that man
can do with his tongue.

16:09.735 --> 16:11.969
Downright illegal.

16:12.070 --> 16:13.971
[ Chuckles ]

16:14.072 --> 16:15.940
Well, I think
that's long enough.

16:16.041 --> 16:16.941
Uh...

16:17.042 --> 16:20.077
Earl was
a real cheap ass.

16:20.178 --> 16:23.314
Here, this is for you.
I doubt he ever tipped you.

16:23.415 --> 16:24.782
Well,
where are you going?

16:24.883 --> 16:28.219
To find Bud, of course --
tell him the good news.

16:28.320 --> 16:29.620
We can get married.

16:29.721 --> 16:31.222
[ Chuckles nervously ]

16:31.323 --> 16:33.591
Oh.

16:33.692 --> 16:35.259
Mm.

16:37.462 --> 16:40.698
[ Door opens, closes ]

16:42.767 --> 16:45.301
Riley: It's really nice of you
coming over.

16:45.402 --> 16:48.371
Taylor: Please, when I heard
that Kyle had resurfaced,

16:48.472 --> 16:51.040
I thought you might need
a little distraction.

16:51.142 --> 16:53.409
Bringing Twinkle over
to play with the kids.

16:53.511 --> 16:55.612
Being a single mother
can't be easy.

16:55.713 --> 16:58.281
I figured you might need
a little, you know...

16:58.382 --> 16:59.449
Help.

16:59.550 --> 17:01.184
Why, Taylor Berkhalter,

17:01.285 --> 17:03.620
I think this is the first
nice thing you've done for me --

17:03.721 --> 17:04.820
ever.

17:04.922 --> 17:06.990
Well, don't go getting
used to it or anything.

17:10.861 --> 17:12.896
You know,
I get why Kyle left.

17:12.997 --> 17:14.897
Oh, and she's back,
ladies and gentlemen --

17:14.999 --> 17:16.566
Taylor Berkhalter.

17:16.666 --> 17:19.002
I'm not saying it's right.
I'm saying, I get it.

17:19.103 --> 17:20.569
Hell's bells,

17:20.671 --> 17:23.772
I'd leave Beau in a heartbeat
if I had the courage.

17:23.874 --> 17:26.309
I think marriage
should be like a business deal.

17:26.410 --> 17:28.411
Every five years,
if it ain't working,

17:28.512 --> 17:30.880
you opt out and move on
to something better.

17:32.716 --> 17:35.118
But then again,
I don't run the world yet.

17:35.219 --> 17:37.754
[ Children laughing ]

17:51.068 --> 17:52.268
Hey.

17:53.938 --> 17:56.973
This time,
it's me bringing you food.

17:57.074 --> 17:58.641
Thank you.

17:58.742 --> 18:01.578
Figured the last thing you'd
want to do tonight is cook.

18:01.679 --> 18:03.913
You can come and join us
if you want.

18:04.014 --> 18:05.515
Uh, no, I-I just --

18:05.616 --> 18:07.884
I really just stopped by
to drop that off.

18:10.321 --> 18:11.955
Make sure you were okay.

18:13.757 --> 18:16.125
I don't know
how okay I am.

18:16.227 --> 18:19.362
But we are not gonna starve
thanks to you.

18:19.463 --> 18:22.432
I can't tell you
how much I appreciate it.

18:22.533 --> 18:24.801
Well, call me
if you need anything, okay?

18:26.937 --> 18:28.938
Love you.

18:33.277 --> 18:35.178
Okay, what are we doing,
you two?

18:35.279 --> 18:37.814
[ Laughs ] We have a surprise
for you.

18:37.915 --> 18:40.116
Keep your eyes closed!
You promised!

18:40.217 --> 18:42.585
Okay, they're closed,
they're closed.

18:44.421 --> 18:45.889
[ Katherine giggles ]

18:45.990 --> 18:48.224
What are you doing here?

18:48.325 --> 18:50.293
I was invited.

18:50.394 --> 18:51.995
We made dinner!

18:52.096 --> 18:54.230
Yeah, come on, look.

19:05.809 --> 19:08.544
And these are for you,
Mom.

19:08.646 --> 19:12.215
I picked all the green ones
out of the cereal for you.

19:13.117 --> 19:14.684
Thank you.
And you.

19:14.785 --> 19:17.854
Not a huge marshmallow fan,
but thank you.

19:17.955 --> 19:19.489
No, silly,
it's green food.

19:19.590 --> 19:22.525
Yeah, we have to eat
something green with every meal.

19:22.626 --> 19:25.929
Well, yes,
I-I meant vegetables,

19:26.030 --> 19:28.598
but this will do
for tonight.

19:28.699 --> 19:30.733
Because
it's a special occasion?

19:32.303 --> 19:35.538
Yeah.
Something like that.

19:36.941 --> 19:40.677
You know, these jelly sandwiches
are so delicious.

19:40.778 --> 19:42.879
Thank you, Daddy.
I made them myself.

19:45.249 --> 19:46.883
Did you?
I'm so impressed.

19:46.984 --> 19:50.053
You know what would make them
even better?

19:50.154 --> 19:51.354
Peanut butter.

19:56.827 --> 19:57.927
What?

19:58.028 --> 19:59.896
W-what I'd say?

19:59.997 --> 20:01.898
Katie's allergic
to peanuts --

20:01.999 --> 20:03.166
had a reaction so bad,

20:03.267 --> 20:04.701
she was in the hospital
for two days.

20:04.802 --> 20:07.537
Sweetheart, I'm sorry.
I didn't know.

20:07.638 --> 20:08.705
Yeah.

20:11.809 --> 20:15.345
This was a stupid idea!

20:15.446 --> 20:17.847
Hey, Travis.

20:21.618 --> 20:23.052
[ Sighs ]

20:41.772 --> 20:44.207
[ Truck door opens ]

20:44.308 --> 20:46.576
[ Truck door closes ]

20:56.954 --> 20:58.221
[ Door closes ]

21:16.206 --> 21:17.974
[ Sighs ]

21:23.347 --> 21:26.115
Look, I realize it's my fault,
but this is crazy.

21:26.216 --> 21:28.584
You and me not talking
like this.

21:28.685 --> 21:30.019
If you say so.

21:30.120 --> 21:31.687
Look, I know you think I just
abandoned Riley and the kids,

21:31.789 --> 21:33.056
but there's more to it
than that.

21:33.157 --> 21:35.324
I mean, everything
that was going on...

21:35.426 --> 21:37.126
it just got
on top of me.

21:37.227 --> 21:38.594
I felt like
I was suffocating.

21:38.695 --> 21:40.897
And the way that it went down,
it's not like I planned it.

21:40.998 --> 21:43.032
It just happened.

21:43.133 --> 21:45.401
I mean, one minute, I'm sitting on
the couch, watching the game,

21:45.502 --> 21:46.769
and the next thing I know,

21:46.870 --> 21:48.471
I'm throwing all my stuff
into a bag

21:48.572 --> 21:49.539
and getting in my truck

21:49.640 --> 21:51.174
and driving west
as fast as I can.

21:51.275 --> 21:52.809
I mean, it wasn't till
that night

21:52.910 --> 21:54.243
when I stopped
outside Amarillo

21:54.344 --> 21:56.145
that it actually hit me
what I had done.

21:56.246 --> 21:59.282
Well, why not turn around
right then and come back?

21:59.383 --> 22:01.317
I don't know.

22:03.587 --> 22:06.089
Shame.

22:06.190 --> 22:07.256
Fear.

22:07.357 --> 22:08.491
You know, confusion.

22:08.592 --> 22:10.193
Cowardice.

22:10.294 --> 22:12.195
Yeah.

22:12.296 --> 22:14.330
Yeah, that too.

22:14.431 --> 22:17.567
Look, I tried so many times
to come back. I swear to you.

22:17.668 --> 22:20.570
But every time,
I just got...

22:20.671 --> 22:22.338
paralyzed, you know?

22:22.439 --> 22:25.108
I was thinking about how much
everybody must hate me, and I...

22:25.209 --> 22:26.309
I couldn't do it.

22:26.410 --> 22:28.845
I don't hate you.

22:28.946 --> 22:30.847
I don't like you
very much right now.

22:30.948 --> 22:33.149
[ Sighs ]

22:33.250 --> 22:35.485
It's just,
I don't get it.

22:35.586 --> 22:38.121
I mean,
h-h-how could you --

22:38.222 --> 22:40.957
how could you do that?

22:42.960 --> 22:44.827
Leave like that
without a word.

22:44.928 --> 22:47.430
I told you, I...

22:47.531 --> 22:49.932
I mean,
Riley and the kids...

22:50.033 --> 22:51.100
and the debt --

22:51.201 --> 22:53.369
no, not them, man.

22:55.506 --> 22:57.907
Not them -- me.

23:00.978 --> 23:02.478
How could you leave me?

23:04.848 --> 23:06.949
I mean, did you ever once
for one second

23:07.050 --> 23:09.118
stop to think about me?

23:09.219 --> 23:11.487
Your brother.

23:11.588 --> 23:14.557
The only family you got.

23:14.658 --> 23:17.059
Hell, Kyle,
after mama and daddy died,

23:17.161 --> 23:19.362
I mean,
all we had was each other.

23:19.463 --> 23:22.298
and then you go off
and disappear, man --

23:22.399 --> 23:24.634
no note,
no word, no nothing!

23:26.970 --> 23:29.672
I mean, do you know --
do you know how that feels?

23:32.075 --> 23:33.309
Not very good,
I imagine.

23:33.410 --> 23:35.144
No, you're damn right
it doesn't!

23:35.245 --> 23:36.913
I mean, I'm looking at you
right now,

23:37.014 --> 23:39.382
and it's like I don't even know
who you are anymore.

23:39.483 --> 23:40.587
Come on, Ev, that's not true.

23:40.612 --> 23:42.218
Yeah, well, what about
those drugs then, huh?!

23:42.219 --> 23:44.253
You took so many of those,
you got hooked.

23:44.354 --> 23:46.822
You had to go to N.A.

23:46.924 --> 23:48.591
How'd you know
about that?

23:48.692 --> 23:50.393
Oh, that was
another fun story.

23:50.494 --> 23:52.295
Yeah, Riley found out
from your --

23:52.396 --> 23:53.963
what was
your friend's name?

23:54.064 --> 23:55.798
Maxine.

23:55.899 --> 23:57.033
Yeah, Maxine.

23:57.134 --> 23:58.568
Yeah,
we had a real good time

23:58.669 --> 24:01.137
wrapping our heads
around that one.

24:03.607 --> 24:06.008
God...I'm so sorry.

24:06.109 --> 24:07.944
You're sorry.
[ Sniffles ]

24:08.045 --> 24:08.978
You're sorry.

24:09.079 --> 24:11.347
Is that -- is that
all you can say?

24:11.448 --> 24:13.282
Is that all you've got?!

24:15.552 --> 24:19.488
You don't know how bad I want
to hurt you right now, Kyle.

24:20.557 --> 24:23.159
I want to hurt you so bad
like you hurt us.

24:23.260 --> 24:25.962
Hit me then.

24:29.399 --> 24:30.833
Kyle: I'm serious.

24:32.502 --> 24:33.502
[ Grunts ]

24:38.609 --> 24:39.775
[ Grunts ]

24:42.379 --> 24:44.580
I ain't gonna hit you.

24:44.681 --> 24:49.285
But I sure as hell
can't respect you anymore.

24:56.126 --> 24:58.894
[ Door opens, closes ]

25:11.903 --> 25:15.338
Mm. Crap.
What time is it?

25:15.440 --> 25:16.473
Almost 8:00.

25:16.574 --> 25:18.542
Mm, good.
I thought I was gonna be late.

25:18.643 --> 25:19.543
No.

25:19.644 --> 25:21.411
Here,
just how you like it.

25:21.512 --> 25:23.980
Ooh. Thank you.

25:24.082 --> 25:26.483
Kids are still sleeping,
too.

25:26.584 --> 25:28.685
They doing okay?

25:28.786 --> 25:31.421
Brave.
Braver than me.

25:31.522 --> 25:33.423
Well,
I don't know about that.

25:33.524 --> 25:34.925
But kids are resilient,

25:35.026 --> 25:37.327
plus they're already
one step ahead.

25:37.428 --> 25:39.796
How so?
They've got you for a mama.

25:42.600 --> 25:44.000
All right...
[ Sighs ]

25:44.102 --> 25:47.437
...on a scale of 1 to 10,
how bad is all this?

25:49.173 --> 25:51.208
I'm scraping 11.

25:52.643 --> 25:54.177
Oh, honey, I'm sorry.

25:54.278 --> 25:56.746
Okay, this is probably
pointless,

25:56.848 --> 25:58.448
but is there anything
I can do?

25:58.549 --> 26:00.951
Do you know anybody
with a time machine

26:01.052 --> 26:03.420
who can spin us all back
a year or so?

26:03.521 --> 26:05.622
Mm, no,
I'm fresh out of those.

26:05.723 --> 26:06.542
Darn.

26:06.567 --> 26:08.525
But knowing what you know
about Kyle, would you --

26:08.526 --> 26:10.026
would you even want
to go back?

26:10.128 --> 26:12.095
Ooh.

26:12.196 --> 26:13.997
Now,
that is a good question.

26:15.366 --> 26:16.600
Kind of hard to put
the genie

26:16.701 --> 26:18.568
back in the bottle
once you let him out.

26:18.669 --> 26:19.836
Mm.

26:19.937 --> 26:22.272
Especially when it's Evan.

26:22.373 --> 26:23.406
You mean Kyle.

26:23.508 --> 26:26.710
No. I mean Evan.

26:26.811 --> 26:27.944
Riley?

26:28.045 --> 26:30.680
Okay, but you swear
no judgments? Pinkie swear?

26:30.781 --> 26:32.082
Yeah, yeah.

26:32.183 --> 26:33.683
Evan and I --

26:33.784 --> 26:35.418
Oh, my God, you did it!
You guys did it!

26:35.520 --> 26:37.554
Shh! Lacey!

26:37.655 --> 26:39.022
No.

26:39.123 --> 26:40.023
Oh.

26:40.124 --> 26:41.258
But we did kiss.

26:41.359 --> 26:44.461
Oh, my God,
that is -- that's the best.

26:44.562 --> 26:45.729
You don't disapprove?

26:45.830 --> 26:46.930
Are you kidding me?

26:47.031 --> 26:49.065
No, I love Evan.
I always have.

26:50.701 --> 26:52.402
But I --

26:52.503 --> 26:54.371
But what?

26:54.472 --> 26:57.274
Well, I just --
I just want to make sure

26:57.375 --> 27:00.744
that you're taking care
of yourself through all this.

27:02.980 --> 27:03.880
Yes.

27:03.981 --> 27:06.283
I am.

27:09.420 --> 27:11.488
What did I do
to get such a good friend?

27:13.691 --> 27:15.759
I don't know.

27:15.860 --> 27:18.295
But you sure are lucky
to have me.

27:18.396 --> 27:19.596
[ Laughs ]

27:19.697 --> 27:21.364
Thank you.

27:21.465 --> 27:23.133
[ Laughs ]

27:23.234 --> 27:25.502
[ Birds chirping ]

27:30.208 --> 27:31.808
I'm back!

27:40.484 --> 27:43.420
Hello, ladies.
Miss me?

27:43.521 --> 27:44.854
Did we just go back
in time?

27:44.956 --> 27:46.590
Girl, last I checked,
you were fired.

27:46.691 --> 27:48.258
Well, I just got rehired.

27:48.359 --> 27:50.327
That's great.
Honey, welcome back.

27:50.428 --> 27:52.829
Hold on, hold on.
By who?

27:52.930 --> 27:54.864
Oh, by me.

27:54.966 --> 27:57.167
The rub of Sugar Land just
wasn't the same without Dee Ann.

27:57.268 --> 27:58.401
Amen.

27:58.502 --> 28:00.070
And I can't thank you enough
for bringing me back.

28:00.171 --> 28:01.204
Touching only one body
at home

28:01.305 --> 28:02.839
was starting to make me
a little cray-cray.

28:02.940 --> 28:04.341
[ Laughter ]

28:04.442 --> 28:07.210
Looks like someone's a little
punch-drunk with power, huh?

28:07.311 --> 28:09.112
I'm sorry. Excuse me?
Come on.

28:09.213 --> 28:11.114
Georgia only gave you temporary
control of this place.

28:11.215 --> 28:12.349
Let's get real.

28:12.450 --> 28:13.917
You ain't nothing but
a glorified babysitter.

28:16.053 --> 28:17.621
Yeah, but she gave it
to me, not you.

28:17.722 --> 28:19.022
Here's the thing, Selena.

28:19.123 --> 28:20.757
Georgia's not here
to protect you,

28:20.858 --> 28:22.525
so back off.

28:24.795 --> 28:25.695
[ Fingers snap ]

28:25.796 --> 28:27.764
Damn.
Double damn.

28:31.936 --> 28:33.770
Well, if it isn't
my old friend.

28:35.973 --> 28:38.675
Yeah, I said we'd be seeing
each other again, didn't I?

28:38.776 --> 28:40.910
Yes, you certainly did.

28:41.012 --> 28:43.346
And what a happy meeting
it is.

28:43.447 --> 28:44.648
Yeah, I'll bet.

28:44.749 --> 28:47.984
Oh, that's for you.

28:48.085 --> 28:49.319
What's that for?

28:49.420 --> 28:52.389
To the beginning
of a beautiful relationship.

28:52.490 --> 28:55.225
I'm sorry.
I don't understand.

28:55.326 --> 28:57.661
Well, I hear, uh,
congratulations are in order.

28:57.762 --> 29:00.130
You're running the place now.
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

29:00.231 --> 29:01.731
I don't know
about all that.

29:01.832 --> 29:03.500
So, what can I do
for you today?

29:03.601 --> 29:06.002
Well, uh...

29:06.103 --> 29:09.372
I got a little deal to propose.
I bet you do.

29:09.473 --> 29:10.573
I would avail myself

29:10.675 --> 29:14.511
of your particular brand
of, uh, services here.

29:14.612 --> 29:16.880
And you gals will get
the full protection of the law.

29:16.981 --> 29:20.517
'Cause you're a nice girl.

29:20.618 --> 29:23.720
And it's real good for nice girls
like you to know guys like me.

29:25.189 --> 29:27.490
Understand?

29:27.591 --> 29:29.726
Just in case
you get into any trouble.

29:34.832 --> 29:36.900
Be seeing you.

29:47.678 --> 29:48.778
[ Door closes ]

29:48.879 --> 29:50.347
[ Sighs ]

29:54.185 --> 29:57.387
Okay, Aunt Lacey.

29:57.488 --> 30:00.657
The kids and I decided we're
gonna go to Emilio's for pizza.

30:04.662 --> 30:06.730
Riley.

30:06.831 --> 30:07.764
You know what?

30:07.865 --> 30:08.798
Can you take the kids
to the bedroom?

30:08.899 --> 30:10.867
Lacey:
Hey, guys, come on.

30:10.968 --> 30:13.570
Let's go into the bedroom
and play. Come on, baby.

30:17.375 --> 30:19.776
Come on.

30:21.779 --> 30:23.680
Are you just never
gonna talk to me again?

30:23.781 --> 30:27.951
You know, this hasn't been
a piece of cake for me, either.

30:28.052 --> 30:31.821
I've been all alone.
I've had no one to talk to.

30:31.922 --> 30:33.957
I've been away
from everyone that I love.

30:34.058 --> 30:36.860
Let's be honest, you're not exactly
the easiest person to come back to.

30:36.961 --> 30:39.362
You son of a bitch!

30:39.463 --> 30:40.764
You son of a bitch!

30:40.865 --> 30:43.032
Hard?! For you?!

30:43.134 --> 30:44.734
Really?!
Hard for you?!

30:44.835 --> 30:46.236
Do you have any idea

30:46.337 --> 30:48.238
how hard it was
to wake up every morning?!

30:48.339 --> 30:51.674
How hard it was
to function every day?!

30:51.776 --> 30:53.610
Hey, hey! No!

30:54.145 --> 30:56.546
You two!
The kids can hear you!

30:56.647 --> 30:57.747
Are you kidding me?
Fine.

30:57.848 --> 30:59.582
Fine.

30:59.683 --> 31:01.785
[ Breathing heavily ]

31:04.054 --> 31:06.956
Riley, please.

31:07.057 --> 31:09.292
I'm sorry.

31:09.393 --> 31:11.194
I will do anything
to make this right, Riley.

31:11.295 --> 31:13.196
Please.

31:14.698 --> 31:16.566
I am the same person
that you fell in love with.

31:16.667 --> 31:18.067
I am not the same.

31:18.169 --> 31:19.869
[ Breathing heavily ]

31:41.225 --> 31:43.593
I'm really proud of y'all.

31:43.694 --> 31:44.794
Why?

31:44.895 --> 31:47.130
Because I know
that it must be real confusing

31:47.231 --> 31:48.531
since your daddy came back.

31:50.167 --> 31:52.368
I know I'm not supposed
to be mad at people,

31:52.470 --> 31:54.437
but I'm kind of mad
at Daddy.

31:54.538 --> 31:57.273
That's okay, baby.

31:57.374 --> 31:59.776
Between us,
I'm mad at him, too.

32:01.679 --> 32:04.247
What about you?
How are you doing?

32:04.348 --> 32:06.883
I'm not mad,
but I'm sad.

32:06.984 --> 32:08.651
What if he goes away
again?

32:13.290 --> 32:14.557
Look, here's the truth.

32:14.658 --> 32:19.596
I don't know if your daddy
is gonna leave again.

32:19.697 --> 32:22.131
But I do know this.

32:22.233 --> 32:25.502
I'm not going anywhere.
Not ever.

32:25.603 --> 32:26.703
Okay?

32:26.804 --> 32:28.705
It's just gonna be
the three of us

32:28.806 --> 32:30.874
forever and ever and ever.

32:30.975 --> 32:33.309
Okay?

32:33.410 --> 32:34.844
Okay.
Okay.

32:34.945 --> 32:35.912
Okay.

32:36.013 --> 32:36.913
Okay.

32:37.014 --> 32:38.615
Okay.

32:38.716 --> 32:41.084
[ Insects chirping ]

32:44.822 --> 32:46.456
You okay?

32:46.557 --> 32:47.991
Getting there.

32:48.092 --> 32:51.060
I got to admit, I never knew
you could fight like that.

32:51.161 --> 32:52.395
Neither did I.

32:52.496 --> 32:54.631
Ooh, I'm glad he didn't break
one of my nails.

32:54.732 --> 32:56.266
That could've
gotten ugly.

32:56.367 --> 32:58.601
[ Both laugh ]

32:58.702 --> 33:00.003
Hey,
do you have the book?

33:00.104 --> 33:01.538
Never got it.
Thought you had it.

33:01.639 --> 33:03.039
Eh, well,
maybe mama has the book.

33:03.140 --> 33:04.207
What book?

33:04.308 --> 33:05.909
The book of life.

33:06.010 --> 33:08.444
Tells you what you're supposed
to do when you get in a fix.

33:08.546 --> 33:10.280
Yeah. Lacey and I
are always marveling

33:10.381 --> 33:13.016
at how other people seem to
just fix their problems so easily.

33:13.117 --> 33:14.851
Mm. We figured someone
must've handed them some book,

33:14.952 --> 33:15.919
told them what to do.

33:16.020 --> 33:17.954
Not us. We're just stumbling
through life,

33:18.055 --> 33:19.489
making all kinds
of mistakes.

33:19.590 --> 33:21.824
Well, hell, when you find it,
I could use a few chapters.

33:21.926 --> 33:23.593
[ Both laugh ]

33:23.694 --> 33:26.963
Okay, well, on that note,
I'm gonna skedaddle.

33:27.064 --> 33:28.698
You gonna be okay?

33:28.799 --> 33:30.600
Absolutely.
I've got this one

33:30.701 --> 33:33.303
just in case any more bad guys
come my way.

33:33.404 --> 33:35.471
From what I saw earlier,
you don't need any protecting.

33:35.573 --> 33:36.906
[ Laughs ]

33:37.007 --> 33:40.443
Okay, then, I'm gone.
See y'all tomorrow.

33:40.544 --> 33:41.811
Love you.
See you later.

33:41.912 --> 33:43.079
Love you, too.

33:47.451 --> 33:49.252
[ Sighing ] Oh, man.

33:51.522 --> 33:52.922
So, can I ask you
something?

33:53.023 --> 33:55.291
Sure.

33:57.027 --> 33:58.528
Where are we?

33:58.629 --> 34:01.230
We are in a good place.

34:01.332 --> 34:04.200
Kyle coming back
doesn't change anything.

34:04.301 --> 34:05.501
It doesn't?

34:05.603 --> 34:07.270
Nope. It doesn't.

34:07.371 --> 34:08.838
At least not for me.

34:08.938 --> 34:11.206
I mean, that Kyle
that showed up on my doorstep

34:11.308 --> 34:13.342
the other night --
I don't want him back.

34:13.444 --> 34:15.411
What if that version
of Kyle changes?

34:15.512 --> 34:17.080
Well...

34:17.181 --> 34:20.049
if wishes were horses,
beggars would ride.

34:20.150 --> 34:22.284
Linette?
You betcha.

34:22.386 --> 34:24.253
[ Both laugh ]

34:24.355 --> 34:27.657
Look, your brother
can't just come back here

34:27.757 --> 34:30.525
with flowers and pretty words
and "I'm sorrys"

34:30.628 --> 34:34.330
and think that things are gonna
go back to the way they were.

34:34.431 --> 34:36.833
That girl is gone.

34:36.934 --> 34:39.002
Well, that's good...

34:39.103 --> 34:41.471
'Cause the woman
I'm staring at right now

34:41.572 --> 34:42.871
is pretty damn amazing.

34:42.973 --> 34:45.375
[ Chuckles ]

34:45.476 --> 34:50.013
Look, I know I'm being selfish
right now,

34:50.114 --> 34:52.181
but, I mean, we never even
got a chance

34:52.282 --> 34:54.050
to see
where this thing could go.

34:54.150 --> 34:55.885
We will.

34:55.985 --> 34:57.654
Yeah?

34:57.755 --> 34:59.255
Yeah.

35:00.324 --> 35:01.457
We will.

35:01.558 --> 35:03.593
[ Insects chirping ]

35:08.832 --> 35:10.800
I'd like that.

35:25.565 --> 35:26.999
[ door opens ]

35:27.100 --> 35:28.233
Hey, honey. You okay?

35:28.335 --> 35:29.768
Got here
as quick as I could.

35:29.869 --> 35:31.570
[ Door closes ]

35:31.671 --> 35:34.973
Why do you keep coming here, anyway?
Because this is my home.

35:35.075 --> 35:36.342
No, it was your home
until you left.

35:37.744 --> 35:40.112
Linette: I brought enough
clothes for a couple of days,

35:40.213 --> 35:41.313
as long as you need me.

35:41.414 --> 35:42.848
Mama, that's real nice, but --
No "buts."

35:42.949 --> 35:45.851
I'm your mother, and a daughter
needs her mom at a time like this.

35:45.952 --> 35:47.653
You know I love you.

35:47.754 --> 35:50.422
I don't need you fighting my battles
for me anymore. That's not why I'm here.

35:50.523 --> 35:53.192
I know you're tougher
than the two of us put together.

35:53.293 --> 35:54.860
Sometimes it doesn't feel
that way.

35:54.961 --> 35:56.462
No, pooh.

35:56.563 --> 35:58.464
If you can get through
your husband leaving you,

35:58.565 --> 36:00.199
you can get through
anything.

36:00.300 --> 36:02.634
Damn straight.
Yeah, what do you know?

36:02.736 --> 36:04.269
You know,
I'm so sick of your bullshit.

36:04.371 --> 36:07.239
Both of you, knock it off.
[ Cellphone ringing ]

36:08.908 --> 36:10.609
[ Cellphone beeps ]

36:10.710 --> 36:13.879
Hey, Georgia.
Everything okay?

36:13.980 --> 36:15.948
[ Sighing ] Oh, crap.
No, I didn't.

36:17.517 --> 36:19.618
Okay. Okay, I understand
how critical it is.

36:19.719 --> 36:20.819
I'll...

36:20.920 --> 36:23.589
Yes, I'll go right now.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

36:23.690 --> 36:25.958
Something came up at work. I got to go.
At this late hour?

36:26.059 --> 36:27.926
It's important. You gonna stay?
Of course.

36:28.027 --> 36:29.828
Don't be here
when I get back.

36:32.832 --> 36:34.700
[ Door opens, closes ]

36:51.751 --> 36:54.386
[ Alarm beeping ]

36:54.487 --> 36:57.356
Shit.

36:57.457 --> 36:59.024
[ Alarm blaring ]

36:59.125 --> 37:00.526
Oh, shit!

37:00.627 --> 37:02.161
[ Blaring continues ]

37:11.204 --> 37:13.372
[ Blaring continues ]

37:13.473 --> 37:15.507
[ Blaring stops ]

37:17.377 --> 37:18.744
Kyle: What was so important
that you had to come up here

37:18.845 --> 37:20.546
in the middle
of the night?

37:20.647 --> 37:23.248
What I do
is none of your business.

37:23.349 --> 37:25.117
What the hell are you doing
here? Are you following me?

37:25.218 --> 37:27.453
Well, you wouldn't talk to me
when anyone else was around,

37:27.554 --> 37:29.488
so I figured I would get you
when you were alone.

37:29.589 --> 37:30.923
That's not a smart move.

37:31.024 --> 37:32.191
Okay, so just leave.

37:32.292 --> 37:35.093
No. I'm not leaving
until I get off my chest

37:35.195 --> 37:38.096
what I need to say.

37:39.466 --> 37:41.633
I love you.

37:41.734 --> 37:43.669
I know
it may not look like it.

37:43.770 --> 37:46.738
And, in fact, I know it may look
just the opposite.

37:46.840 --> 37:49.942
But it's because I love you
that I left.

37:50.043 --> 37:53.545
Riley, come on. I was no good to you
or the kids the way that I was.

37:53.646 --> 37:55.047
I was messed up.

37:55.148 --> 37:57.583
My head -- my head
was in a dark place.

38:01.187 --> 38:03.355
You know...

38:03.456 --> 38:05.524
[ Sighs ]

38:05.625 --> 38:07.860
...Evan told me...

38:07.961 --> 38:10.662
that you found out
that I was abusing those pills.

38:10.763 --> 38:12.130
[ Sighs ]

38:12.232 --> 38:14.600
And I'm so sorry that you
had to find out like that

38:14.701 --> 38:16.602
and for not telling you
myself

38:16.703 --> 38:18.470
and for not letting you
in.

38:18.571 --> 38:21.707
All right, it's just that
I got so bad that...

38:21.808 --> 38:25.644
I was scared that if I stayed
that I might...

38:25.745 --> 38:27.613
that I might
do something.

38:27.714 --> 38:31.383
All right, so I left.

38:31.484 --> 38:34.219
I left to get my head
screwed on straight.

38:34.320 --> 38:36.488
All right,
I never thought about

38:36.589 --> 38:39.091
what it would do
to you and the kids.

38:39.192 --> 38:40.993
And I'm sorry.

38:41.094 --> 38:42.227
But I knew the only way

38:42.328 --> 38:44.496
I'd ever be able to take care
of you again

38:44.597 --> 38:46.665
was if I took care of myself,
and I did.

38:46.766 --> 38:48.534
All right, I did.
I'm here now.

38:48.635 --> 38:52.871
And I will do anything...
to make this right.

38:57.844 --> 38:59.645
Please?

39:02.215 --> 39:03.415
Riley, please.

39:05.652 --> 39:07.519
This was never about
loving you.

39:07.620 --> 39:10.689
I mean, that doesn't get lost
in bills and mortgages.

39:10.790 --> 39:13.559
All right, I never stopped
loving you for a second.

39:13.660 --> 39:17.429
Baby,
you're my whole life.

39:17.530 --> 39:19.731
[ Sighs ]

39:21.067 --> 39:23.201
Come on.

39:23.303 --> 39:27.372
Are you really just gonna stand
there and not say anything?

39:27.473 --> 39:30.275
Don't you care anything
about where I've been

39:30.376 --> 39:31.877
and what I've been doing?

39:31.978 --> 39:36.081
Or why I'm here now?

39:40.853 --> 39:43.755
Fine.

39:43.856 --> 39:46.458
Fine, Kyle.
Why are you here?

39:49.729 --> 39:52.531
I heard
you were in trouble.

40:21.127 --> 40:22.961
Are you in trouble?

40:22.986 --> 40:26.986
